\lim_{k \to + \infty} \log_k(k^a + k^b) = \lim_{k \to + \infty} \frac{\ln(k^a + k^b)}{\ln k}
\lim_{k \to +\infty} \frac{\frac{k^a \ln k + k^b \ln k}{k^a + k^b}}{\frac{1}{k}} = \lim_{k \to +\infty} \ln k \frac{k^{a +1} + k^{b + 1}}{k^a + k^b} = \lim_{k \to + \infty} \ln k \frac{k^{a + 1 -b} + k}{k^{a - b} + 1} \\ = \lim_{k \to +\infty} k \ln k \frac{k^{a - b} + 1}{k^{a - b} + 1} = \lim_{k \to +\infty} k \ln k = + \infty
